Corlears Street, at the N.W. corner of Monroe Street, showing the 2 story structure listed as the New York Railways Company.

March 4, 1937

Berenice Abbott, photo
Federal Art Project

Monroe Street, west from a point between Corlears and Jackson Street's, and across the latter, showing tenements being demolished for the City sponsored housing project, The Vladeck City Houses. These are on this side of Jackson Street, occupying the S. E. and N. E. corners. The nondescript structures beyond will be replaced with the government sponsored project, Vladeck Houses.

1: May 7, 1939
21 June 24, 1939
